article.headline: Campbell 85, Jacksonville 73
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -- Campbell won its first game of the season Saturday, beating Jacksonville 85-73 behind 21 points from Tarick Johnson. The Camels (1-13, 1-6 Atlantic Sun Conference) gave Robbie Laing his first career victory as a Division I head coach and ended an 18-game losing streak that stretched back to last season. Anthony Atkinson added 17 points and six assists, while Diego Aguiar recorded his first career double-double with 10 points and 10 rebounds. Haminn Quaintance led Jacksonville (6-8, 1-6) with 18 points and eight rebounds before fouling out with 2:03 remaining. David Lee had 17 points and seven boards for the Dolphins, who lost their fourth-straight game. The lead changed 15 times and there were 11 ties in the game. Campbell led 71-69 with 2:55 to go after the Dolphins broke a nearly four-minute scoring drought with a 3-pointer from Lee. Johnson countered with his own 3-pointer to start an 11-0 run that sealed the win. Only North Carolina A&T (0-14) remains winless among Division I schools after the Aggies lost to Coppin State 64-42 on Saturday night.
